Class Egypt

  • java.lang.Object
    • homework2.Egypt

  • public class Egypt
extends java.lang.Object
    Egypt is a type o civilization. It has the same core as Qin Dynasty and Roman Empire. The main difference is the Desert and the ability to build a Pyramid. Also if you are am Egyptian you can practice Hieroglyphics. Getters: getCoalMine() // returns mine getRiver() // returns river getNumSettlements() // returns count getStrategy() // returns strategy getStrategyLevel() // returns strategy.getStrategyLevel() getTechnology() // returns tech getTreasury() // returns treasury getPopulation() // returns populations getSettlements() // returns settlementArray getDesert() // returns desert Constructors: Egypt() // sets variables to the default values Methods: settle(Settlement settlement) // adds a settlement in settlements array buildPyramid(Settlement s) // builds a pyramid practiceHieroglyphics() // civilians practice Hieroglyphics
